--- RED cause analysis (acceptance-first first run, before fixes) ---
TEST-011.5/.6: select-agent-model.ps1's successful (non-BLOCKED escalation)
path performs no native/external command and never calls an explicit
`exit N`, so $LASTEXITCODE after `& $selectModelPs1 ...` is stale (left over
from an earlier native command in this suite, e.g. the cycle-limit
Escalate-Human leg's exit 1) and is not a meaningful signal for this call
shape -- matching the existing tests/agent-model-routing.tests.ps1
convention, which likewise never checks $LASTEXITCODE for this script's
successful/JSON-emitting path. Fix: assert on the JSON content only for
these two legs (dropped the $rc dependency).
TEST-018.2: the intended mutation ("remove the \b word-boundary anchors from
the Select-String pattern in a temp copy") was implemented with a broken
[regex]::Escape(...) double-escaping bug that produced an invalid/empty
search pattern, so the .Replace() call silently matched nothing and the
subsequently-invoked mutated script crashed with a null Pattern argument.
Fix: replaced the regex-based approach with a plain literal
[string]::Replace() substitution of the exact source snippet
`"\b" + [regex]::Escape($TaskId) + "\b"` -> `[regex]::Escape($TaskId)`.

(This suite has no separate genuine RED run before its own file existed --
unlike T-002's tests/lib/loop-driver.sh, T-004 introduces no new shared
